ists who study landscapes to document Arctic change using large datasets. We are creating software to search for, identify, and study topographic patterns and change in landscapes underlain by permafrost, step-by-step guides on how to use it, and educational materials to teach the next generation of geoscientists. We focus on the Arctic because while there are now many new datasets of this remote environment, their size and complexity can make them daunting to use for asking science questions. Our goal is to empower undergraduate researchers to collect input data for teaching computers how to find landscape disturbances and to use those data for their own research questions.","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"UpBm3J6sfa"}],"key":"zsdF7NlT9w"}],"key":"RSLgLNvGkE"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"image","url":"/osdf-cookbook/build/pycogss-logo-078342e84e520afc06defa52b53fb6f2.png","alt":"PyCoGSS logo","width":"300px","align":"center","key":"kTJRDunhLE","urlSource":"../thumbnails/pycogss-logo.png"}],"key":"BAg8ekcVag"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"thematicBreak","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"mZoQj5B9PE"}],"key":"TB9EXROIj0"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Overview","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"jlGddvrnyq"}],"identifier":"overview","label":"Overview","html_id":"overview","implicit":true,"key":"pYRvnlBmvs"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In this notebook you will learn about spectral data and how it can be used to track vegetation change. You will learn why it is important to track vegetation change across the Arctic, a